two in number, and each of several barrels’ capacity. When not in use, they 
are kept remarkably clean. Sometimes they are polished with soapstone and sand, 
till they shine within like silver punch-bowls. During the night-watches some 
cynical old sailors will crawl into them and coil themselves away there for a 
